magnet can be described by nearest-neighbor singlet dimers, it is a\ndiamond valence bond crystal, and, a contrario, that, if the system is a\nquantum spin liquid, it has to involve long-range singlets, consistent with the\nalgebraic spin liquid scenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 30 Jul 2017 20:21:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 22 Dec 2017 08:31:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-07"}
